# Civilization Stability Engineering

## Research Topic

Civilization Stability Engineering studies how advanced civilizations can survive technological singularity and systemic complexity growth.

## Problem

As civilization complexity increases, governance capacity may not keep up.

Complexity ↑
Governance ↓

This creates systemic instability.

## Hypothesis

A civilization needs stable mechanisms to survive high-complexity transitions.

Possible mechanisms include:

- Civilization Consensus Protocol
- Civilization Operating System
- Civilization Immune System
- Civilization Evolution Engine

## Research Goal

Prevent civilization collapse during technological transition.

Upgrade civilization instead of system reset.
